cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA

This paper is about a localization framework for robots using convolutional neural networks for object detection and pose estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques, such as object detection, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of neural networks for identification and orientation estimation could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the framework in swarm robotics, which could suggest a potential fit for cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
